      "rationale": "FDA pump experimental data acquired at 2500 and 3500 RPM across flow rates of 2.5, 5.0, and 7.5 L/min. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water) properties matched to within 2% of CFD inlet conditions. Inlet velocity profiles derived from upstream pipe measurements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) within 25% of experimental mean across all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted NIH values compared against experimental measurements from FDA benchmark dataset. Mean absolute percentage error was 14.7% across all operating points. Worst-case deviation of 22.1% observed at 2500 RPM / 7.5 L/min. All predictions within acceptance threshold. Achieved level 3 reflects quantitative comparison with uncertainty bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
