      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoI (NIH, pressure head) directly correspond to regulatory submission QoI for hemolysis risk assessment.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI in both validation and COU is the normalized index of hemolysis computed via the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. Secondary QoI of pump pressure head directly supports operating condition identification. Both QoIs are identical between validation activities and intended COU application."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
